WEBVTT

00:08.708 --> 00:12.145
<i>Be very welcome, everyone,</i>
<i>to</i> La Quinta Marcha.

00:12.245 --> 00:14.848
<i>Today we have a group
that is hella bodacious.</i>

00:14.914 --> 00:17.717
<i>In tonight's show, my dad,</i>

00:17.784 --> 00:21.388
<i>the king of fried chicken.</i>

00:21.488 --> 00:24.491
<i>May I?
Looks kind of burnt, huh?</i>

00:24.557 --> 00:25.492
<i>Do you have anything to say?</i>

00:25.558 --> 00:27.894
<i>Stop it, Sandra,
I'm burning it.</i>

00:27.961 --> 00:29.829
PAULA:<i> Ugh, that smells</i>
<i>terrible.</i>

00:29.929 --> 00:31.531
<i>No, put that
obnoxious thing down,</i>

00:31.598 --> 00:32.732
<i>you always make me look ugly.</i>

00:32.799 --> 00:34.401
[toy keyboard playing]

00:34.467 --> 00:35.702
MARIO:<i> Disgusting.</i>

00:35.802 --> 00:37.771
PAULA:<i> Do you want pizza?</i>

00:37.837 --> 00:39.572
SANDRA:<i> [chuckles]</i>

00:41.074 --> 00:44.844
<i>As you can all see,
the kid isn't the next Mozart.</i>

00:46.112 --> 00:48.014
<i>Shit.
[groans]</i>

00:48.081 --> 00:49.616
SANDRA:<i> Shit is what</i>
<i>you're playing.</i>

00:49.682 --> 00:50.984
<i>Watch and learn.</i>

00:52.352 --> 00:53.553
<i>Watch this.</i>

00:54.788 --> 00:57.323
<i>[keyboard playing]</i>

00:57.390 --> 00:59.759
<i>[singing in Spanish]</i>

01:17.277 --> 01:18.645
<i>[chuckles]</i>

01:18.711 --> 01:19.813
MARIO:<i> Hey, kids,</i>
<i>weather's nice.</i>

01:19.879 --> 01:21.481
<i>Why don't we go out for dinner?</i>

01:21.548 --> 01:23.883
<i>Oh, I have plans, Dad,
and I'm already late.</i>

01:23.950 --> 01:24.784
MARIO:<i> What?</i>
<i>Plans, with whom?</i>

01:24.884 --> 01:26.186
SANDRA:<i> With Eva and Molina,</i>

01:26.286 --> 01:27.787
<i>the Almanzora party, the fair.</i>

01:27.887 --> 01:30.190
PAULA:<i> I'll meet you later at</i>
<i>the shooting stand and teach you</i>

01:30.290 --> 01:31.791
<i>- how to shoot, okay?
- Okay.</i>

01:31.891 --> 01:33.159
<i>My girl?
Don't even think about it.</i>

01:33.226 --> 01:35.361
<i>- [scoffs]
- Hey, can I have some money</i>

01:35.428 --> 01:35.962
<i>to get on a ride?</i>

01:42.769 --> 01:44.304
<i>Are you kidding me, Dad?</i>

01:44.404 --> 01:46.673
<i>That's not enough for any game
at the carnival.</i>

01:51.044 --> 01:52.679
<i>Thank you!
You are the best!</i>

01:52.745 --> 01:54.280
<i>[laughing]
Later!</i>

01:54.347 --> 01:55.949
<i>- I want you here at 11:00.
- Bye, Dad.</i>

01:56.049 --> 01:57.784
<i>- Bye-bye, have fun.
- 12:00 then.</i>

01:57.884 --> 01:59.886
<i>You know she played you,
right?</i>

01:59.953 --> 02:01.554
<i>- What?</i>
JAVI:<i> Yeah, she did, Dad.</i>

02:01.654 --> 02:02.956
<i>Dad, look, come here.</i>

02:04.124 --> 02:06.159
<i>- You know what?
- Hm?</i>

02:06.226 --> 02:07.927
<i>[laughing]
You've been chumped out.</i>

02:07.994 --> 02:09.729
<i>- What?
- You are a chump.</i>

02:09.796 --> 02:11.631
<i>- What'd you call me?
- No, no! Please, I mean it!</i>

02:11.731 --> 02:13.333
<i>- What'd you call me, huh?
- No, Dad. Please don't, Dad!</i>

02:13.399 --> 02:15.135
<i>Please stop it! No!
No tickling, I mean it. Come on.</i>

02:15.201 --> 02:16.302
MARIO:<i> Oh, you think</i>
<i>you're so funny, right?</i>

02:16.402 --> 02:17.370
<i>Put me down, please, Dad.
No!</i>

02:17.437 --> 02:18.805
<i>Well, we are going
to the fair.</i>

02:18.872 --> 02:19.973
<i>Come on, put me down. No!</i>

02:20.039 --> 02:21.975
<i>- Okay?
- Be careful!</i>

02:22.041 --> 02:23.109
<i>No!</i>

02:29.649 --> 02:31.184
Hey, Mom,
I'm going to the fair.

02:35.922 --> 02:38.558
FEMALE VOICE: Olivia,
where are you going?

02:43.429 --> 02:44.964
Olivia.

02:47.567 --> 02:48.801
Hello?

02:56.676 --> 02:58.912
[panicked breathing]

03:01.214 --> 03:03.783
Olivia, can I tell you
something?

03:03.883 --> 03:05.185
Who said that?

03:29.209 --> 03:30.843
[creaking]

03:44.991 --> 03:47.160
[gasping]

03:53.633 --> 03:55.368
[ghost screaming]

03:55.435 --> 03:57.804
[knocking]

03:57.870 --> 03:59.372
BEA: Olivia?

03:59.439 --> 04:01.174
[knocking continues]

04:03.610 --> 04:04.544
Why are you still here?

04:04.644 --> 04:06.946
Did you doze off?

04:07.046 --> 04:08.748
We were meeting at 6:00.

04:13.586 --> 04:13.987
Olivia, are you okay?

04:16.756 --> 04:18.758
Yeah, you go on ahead.

04:18.825 --> 04:21.127
I'll meet you later
near the bumper cars, please.

04:24.597 --> 04:24.998
All right.

04:36.476 --> 04:38.044
[grunting]

04:39.412 --> 04:42.248
[sighs]

04:42.315 --> 04:44.050
- Damn it! Damn it!
- I'll try.

04:44.117 --> 04:45.351
- No, no, no, I wanna try.
- No, dude, let me do it.

04:45.451 --> 04:46.986
- I wanna go first because--
- Leave it to me,

04:47.086 --> 04:48.054
- I know what to do.
- What do you know?

04:48.121 --> 04:49.489
Get back, get back.
All right.

04:49.555 --> 04:51.190
What did the ugly
subway guy say in "Ghost"?

04:51.291 --> 04:52.959
Now, think like
a ghost, man.

04:53.026 --> 04:55.528
I mean, it can't be difficult.

04:55.595 --> 04:57.263
[sighs]

04:57.363 --> 04:58.564
What the hell?

05:03.069 --> 05:04.237
They take out the Mortise,
she leaves us a book

05:04.304 --> 05:06.239
with all the answers,
and we can't open it.

05:06.306 --> 05:09.375
It's like Obi-Wan giving
his lightsaber to Luke

05:09.442 --> 05:11.878
and it has no batteries.

05:11.944 --> 05:13.246
They killed the Mortise
for helping us

05:13.313 --> 05:14.881
and we're wasting time
doing nothing.

05:14.947 --> 05:16.549
What should we do?
For all we know,

05:16.649 --> 05:17.884
there are Ghost Riders all over.

05:18.918 --> 05:20.520
What if we go find them first?

05:21.988 --> 05:23.956
The celebrations start today.
The whole town will be there.

05:24.023 --> 05:24.924
Did you listen
to the Mortise?

05:26.793 --> 05:28.294
Bloodthirsty assassins.

05:29.395 --> 05:32.932
Shadow-born beings,
bearers of evil.

05:32.999 --> 05:33.966
Tremendously strong,

05:34.033 --> 05:36.936
intelligent,
almost invincible.

05:38.805 --> 05:41.240
♪♪♪

05:58.324 --> 05:59.592
She actually said
that if we see any,

05:59.692 --> 06:02.228
we'd better run fast.

06:02.328 --> 06:05.565
They're dangerous, man.
Dangerous as hell.

06:06.666 --> 06:08.434
Yeah.

06:08.534 --> 06:10.770
But we know something now.

06:10.837 --> 06:12.638
The light makes us invisible.

06:13.773 --> 06:15.675
It's still hours
before it gets dark.

06:15.775 --> 06:17.210
We don't even know
how to kill them,

06:17.276 --> 06:19.412
- or what are their weak points.
- Our necks are on the line.

06:19.479 --> 06:21.080
Come on, guys,
we are not splitting up.

06:21.147 --> 06:21.748
And we'll be back
in a couple of hours.

06:21.848 --> 06:24.150
What about the book?

06:24.250 --> 06:25.918
We can't just take off
and leave it here

06:25.985 --> 06:27.120
for everybody to see.

06:27.186 --> 06:29.722
I'm staying.
I'm staying.

06:30.523 --> 06:31.991
Just so nobody grabs it.

06:32.091 --> 06:33.926
That's the reason
I'm staying here.

06:33.993 --> 06:35.228
Just please be careful.

06:35.328 --> 06:36.562
Don't take your eyes
off the book.

06:36.629 --> 06:36.929
Come on.

06:39.599 --> 06:41.134
What if we run
into a revenant?

06:41.200 --> 06:43.736
I don't know, Alvaro.
I don't know.

06:45.037 --> 06:46.773
But my sister is locked up
somewhere in town,

06:46.839 --> 06:48.007
and those guys know where.

06:52.678 --> 06:54.113
[sighs]

06:55.748 --> 06:57.049
♪♪♪

07:12.198 --> 07:14.767
[horns honking,
people chattering]

07:21.107 --> 07:24.076
GIRL: Hey, what's up, everybody?
Hey, hello!

07:36.189 --> 07:38.624
The food stalls are over there.

07:38.724 --> 07:41.194
Hey, hello, kiddos!
Hey!

07:44.630 --> 07:48.568
[people cheering]

07:52.438 --> 07:55.641
♪♪♪

08:23.870 --> 08:25.037
Did you notice that?

08:25.104 --> 08:27.907
- Notice what?
- No, nothing.

08:42.054 --> 08:43.022
Javi?

08:44.724 --> 08:45.024
Javi!

08:47.493 --> 08:49.662
Javi!

09:00.840 --> 09:01.908
[sighs]

09:03.376 --> 09:05.945
Let me see.
Come on, Quino.

09:08.481 --> 09:11.851
[blowing]

09:13.119 --> 09:14.554
Hey.
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

09:14.654 --> 09:17.223
No, no!
No!

09:48.454 --> 09:49.855
That's my drawing.

09:50.523 --> 09:52.892
[door closes]

10:28.294 --> 10:30.830
GIRL 1: Wanna go?
GIRL 2: Okay, yeah.

10:30.930 --> 10:33.466
[people chattering]

10:40.506 --> 10:42.008
Javi?

10:55.388 --> 10:57.757
♪♪♪

11:23.349 --> 11:25.384
[people laughing]

11:25.484 --> 11:26.352
MAN: No, slow down.

11:26.452 --> 11:27.753
Wait, bro,
we'll get lost too.

11:27.853 --> 11:28.988
WOMAN: [laughing]
Wait!

11:29.088 --> 11:32.625
MAN: Hey, bro,
check this out.

11:32.725 --> 11:32.925
WOMAN: Where is the exit?
MAN: Look at me.

11:35.094 --> 11:37.029
Did you see?
Bro, you look so short.

11:40.366 --> 11:42.435
- Javi?
JAVI: Al!

11:42.535 --> 11:44.603
Al, there's one of them here!

11:44.670 --> 11:45.071
How do you know that?

11:47.273 --> 11:48.441
Where is it?

11:59.585 --> 12:00.853
Javi!

12:04.023 --> 12:05.958
- Javi?
- Al!

12:11.063 --> 12:11.931
Al!

13:03.082 --> 13:04.016
WOMAN: Run, come on!
MAN: Quickly, come on.

13:04.083 --> 13:05.251
- Come on, run!
- Hurry up!

13:05.317 --> 13:06.786
Javi?

13:10.256 --> 13:10.823
Al.

13:10.923 --> 13:12.091
Al, did you see her?

13:17.663 --> 13:18.063
She's getting away!

13:24.603 --> 13:25.070
Javi!

14:25.431 --> 14:26.599
Javi!

14:26.665 --> 14:30.669
[high-pitch ringing]

14:30.769 --> 14:32.037
Javi!

14:44.049 --> 14:45.985
[gasps]
Oh, shit.

14:48.754 --> 14:51.123
[high-pitch ringing]

15:11.744 --> 15:13.646
[panicked breathing]

15:18.350 --> 15:19.518
Ah!

15:24.890 --> 15:25.958
- You?
- Run.

15:28.694 --> 15:30.095
Come on, hurry!

15:34.133 --> 15:35.834
[growling]

17:06.291 --> 17:07.593
Malena.

17:15.534 --> 17:17.603
[both panting]

17:19.371 --> 17:20.572
What are you doing here?

17:20.639 --> 17:22.674
Saving your ass,
apparently, bro.

17:22.775 --> 17:24.676
But you... you left us.

17:24.743 --> 17:27.746
Well, obviously, I didn't.

17:27.846 --> 17:28.914
Where have you been
since then?

17:29.014 --> 17:30.582
Well, minding some stuff?

17:30.682 --> 17:32.584
- What fucking stuff?
- Where are the others?

17:32.684 --> 17:33.986
There are zombies everywhere.

17:34.086 --> 17:35.754
You can't be minding stuff.

17:35.854 --> 17:37.523
Why is this
your business?

17:37.589 --> 17:39.024
Are you my mother now,
or what?

17:39.124 --> 17:39.925
QUINO: Al.

17:43.629 --> 17:44.763
What are you doing here?

17:44.830 --> 17:46.732
You too?
Are you my father?

17:47.633 --> 17:48.000
What happened?

17:59.678 --> 18:03.015
♪♪♪

19:52.491 --> 19:54.760
[gasps]

20:16.648 --> 20:16.949
Your food.

20:30.395 --> 20:32.631
Ugh!

20:33.632 --> 20:36.668
This shit is gross.

20:36.768 --> 20:41.440
I imagine they're some sort
of shrimp or mussels.

20:43.909 --> 20:45.944
Why do they feed us this crap?

20:46.044 --> 20:47.746
Why do they wash us
with these soaps?

20:47.846 --> 20:50.282
- Huh?
- I don't know.

20:50.349 --> 20:53.051
But we have to endure,
be stronger.

20:53.118 --> 20:54.953
And for that,
we need to eat.

20:55.053 --> 20:56.588
Tell me who cares
if we're gonna end up

20:56.688 --> 20:57.723
in a fucking ditch,
goddamn it!

20:57.789 --> 20:59.491
Don't say that.
We'll get out of here.

20:59.558 --> 21:01.159
We will be dead.
They'll cut us up like rabbits.

21:01.226 --> 21:02.928
- Don't you get it?
- Shut it!

21:02.995 --> 21:04.229
Your father will have to go
to the station

21:04.329 --> 21:05.631
to identify your body
and there's nothing--

21:05.731 --> 21:06.965
She said shut it!

21:10.469 --> 21:13.839
[sobbing]

21:35.193 --> 21:37.029
Remember that day
at Cala Chica?

21:42.067 --> 21:45.604
The jump from the cliff
was amazing.

21:47.439 --> 21:49.574
- [laughing]
- Especially for the guys

21:49.641 --> 21:52.010
hanging out at the joint.

21:52.077 --> 21:55.047
They saw Malena's cha-chas
because she lost her top.

21:56.682 --> 21:57.949
I've always had nice boobs.

21:58.050 --> 22:01.253
And the one
who was obsessed,

22:01.320 --> 22:03.922
he walked us to the mall,
remember?

22:03.989 --> 22:06.191
Then he invited us
to the cinema.

22:07.759 --> 22:09.628
That preppy from Altea,

22:09.728 --> 22:10.429
that man was uglier
than my ass.

22:10.529 --> 22:13.765
[all laughing]

22:13.832 --> 22:15.434
And we left in a rush that day

22:15.534 --> 22:17.803
before they turned on
the lights.

22:19.771 --> 22:21.173
What did we watch?

22:24.443 --> 22:25.811
"Pretty Woman."

22:29.247 --> 22:33.752
What I wouldn't give
to watch "Pretty Woman."

22:37.456 --> 22:40.792
Do you really think
we'll get out of here alive?

22:52.270 --> 22:54.606
[sobbing]

23:00.645 --> 23:03.081
[singing in Spanish]

23:34.613 --> 23:36.948
[music playing]

23:59.905 --> 24:01.039
Bea, I'm sorry.
I had to do one thing.

24:01.106 --> 24:02.441
- Olivia, where were you?
- I'm sorry.

24:02.507 --> 24:03.275
I was worried,
I thought something

24:03.375 --> 24:05.210
might have happened to you.

24:05.277 --> 24:07.212
- Bea, you have to--
- Oh, so now you're leaving?

24:07.279 --> 24:08.513
- Bea, there's something...
- What's the matter with you?

24:08.613 --> 24:09.481
- I need to tell you urgently.
- No, Olivia.

24:09.548 --> 24:10.882
- Please.
- What is it? Tell me!

24:10.949 --> 24:12.050
- Come on.
- Come with me.

24:12.117 --> 24:13.185
- Olivia, wait!
- Hurry!

24:18.423 --> 24:21.560
[sighs]

24:21.626 --> 24:23.328
You had one job, dude.

24:23.395 --> 24:25.797
You only had to watch
the book for two hours.

24:25.864 --> 24:26.932
I got distracted
just for a second.

24:26.998 --> 24:29.801
I turned around
and it was gone.

24:30.669 --> 24:32.070
Shit, I screwed it.

24:32.170 --> 24:34.172
- Sorry, dude.
- No, you screwed us!

24:34.239 --> 24:35.474
You're an idiot.

24:35.574 --> 24:37.108
You don't learn anything,
you keep doing this.

24:37.209 --> 24:39.544
- You're overreacting.
- I will if I want to!

24:39.644 --> 24:40.912
He screwed us big time.

24:41.012 --> 24:44.015
He just had to stick
to the plan.

24:44.082 --> 24:45.584
The plan also was
to stay together,

24:45.684 --> 24:47.285
and you took off as soon
as we set foot in the fair.

24:47.352 --> 24:48.520
I didn't take off.

24:48.587 --> 24:49.654
I went after one
of those zombies.

24:49.721 --> 24:51.756
- I was touched.
- Oh, you were touched?

24:51.823 --> 24:54.426
Well, I was attacked.

24:54.526 --> 24:56.528
And you left me alone in there
with one of them.

24:56.595 --> 24:57.796
Sorry to be a little
uptight about this,

24:57.896 --> 25:00.932
but if you didn't know,
they've got my sister.

25:00.999 --> 25:03.568
My father's devastated.

25:03.635 --> 25:06.037
- You know it's my family!
- Hey, take it easy now.

25:07.439 --> 25:10.909
Javi, Javi, we all have
a family too, remember?

25:11.009 --> 25:13.545
And we're never
going to see them again,

25:13.645 --> 25:16.114
because of you,
for helping you.

25:16.615 --> 25:18.683
Yeah?

25:20.185 --> 25:22.721
If this is helping, you better
get the hell out of here.

25:53.118 --> 25:54.085
Javi.

25:57.989 --> 25:58.023
Al.

26:07.599 --> 26:09.801
MAN: If you hit it,
I'll give you an extra shot.

26:09.868 --> 26:12.237
[people chattering]

26:17.742 --> 26:19.077
That one.

26:19.144 --> 26:20.045
I think the other is funnier.

26:23.415 --> 26:25.750
MAN: Fine, but after that,
you get one more, okay?

26:31.122 --> 26:32.924
Are you gonna be long, honey?

26:37.896 --> 26:40.398
Do your thing,
don't mind that guy.

26:40.465 --> 26:42.601
Concentrate.

26:42.667 --> 26:45.036
Take a deep breath.

26:45.103 --> 26:47.505
And when you let it out,
it's time.

26:47.606 --> 26:50.809
[gun popping]

26:50.875 --> 26:52.911
This shotgun has been rigged.

26:53.011 --> 26:55.046
- Don't like it, don't play.
- [scoffs]

26:55.113 --> 26:56.548
Hey.
Hey, hey, wait.

26:56.648 --> 26:57.716
- Where are you going?
- That guy's mocking us.

26:57.782 --> 27:00.385
[scoffs]
And the best move

27:00.485 --> 27:01.686
is just walking away?

27:01.753 --> 27:02.921
You heard the guy.

27:02.988 --> 27:05.390
His stand, his rules.
What now?

27:05.490 --> 27:08.627
Quitting is not an option.
It's not, never.

27:11.062 --> 27:13.331
You're smarter than that guy.

27:15.433 --> 27:17.736
Show me.

27:17.802 --> 27:19.771
Beat him at his own game.

27:21.439 --> 27:22.674
Look for the flaw.

27:22.774 --> 27:24.409
Look for what doesn't fit.

27:24.476 --> 27:25.944
The trick.

27:28.246 --> 27:31.483
There's always something
that no one else sees

27:31.549 --> 27:32.717
but that is there.

27:32.784 --> 27:34.686
Trust me.

27:34.753 --> 27:37.355
When you finally find it,

27:37.455 --> 27:39.824
that's when you know
you've won.

27:47.966 --> 27:49.067
Find the flaw.

27:52.003 --> 27:53.571
- Perfect!
- Super!

27:53.638 --> 27:55.106
Do you see that?

28:00.912 --> 28:02.547
[gun popping]

28:02.647 --> 28:04.649
MAN: Whenever you're ready,
gentlemen, go for it.

28:06.151 --> 28:07.686
- Thanks.
- Ladies and gentlemen,

28:07.752 --> 28:09.320
children of all ages,

28:09.387 --> 28:11.523
welcome to the greatest show
on Earth,

28:11.589 --> 28:13.024
the Almanzora Festival.

28:16.094 --> 28:17.796
Do you wanna grab
a drink with me?

28:17.896 --> 28:20.231
[people chattering]

28:24.969 --> 28:27.872
- I won this. [laughing]
- Geez.

28:55.266 --> 28:56.835
Hey!

29:00.605 --> 29:00.972
BEA: What?

29:11.449 --> 29:12.917
What?

29:12.984 --> 29:14.652
Did you hear that?

29:15.720 --> 29:17.055
No, what was it?

29:18.556 --> 29:20.158
Nothing.

29:28.533 --> 29:29.868
EVA: Help!

29:29.968 --> 29:31.469
We need help, it's Sandra!

29:31.569 --> 29:32.904
MALENA: Somebody, please!

29:33.004 --> 29:34.372
EVA: Help us, please!

29:35.974 --> 29:37.909
- You're going to be all right.
- We did everything you told us,

29:38.009 --> 29:40.311
but now she won't stop
throwing up.

29:40.411 --> 29:42.347
What's wrong?
What did you give us?

29:42.447 --> 29:43.848
She's sick!

29:45.450 --> 29:46.851
Sandra, please fight.

29:46.918 --> 29:49.287
[girls sobbing]

29:51.589 --> 29:54.392
- Get her out.
EVA: No, please, ma'am, don't!

29:54.492 --> 29:55.827
- Please, Sandra!
- What are you doing?

29:55.927 --> 29:58.396
No!
Put her down!

29:58.463 --> 29:59.664
Sandra!

29:59.764 --> 30:02.367
Sandra!
Let go of her!

30:02.433 --> 30:03.668
Bring her back!

30:33.364 --> 30:35.834
You're going to be fine.
You'll see.

30:41.873 --> 30:43.675
I'll go get something
for your fever.

30:45.677 --> 30:46.010
Stay here.

30:49.447 --> 30:50.014
Stay here.

30:54.252 --> 30:54.919
[whimpering]

30:58.289 --> 30:59.691
Don't leave me alone.

31:02.227 --> 31:03.561
Stay here.

31:07.065 --> 31:08.066
Stay.

31:18.543 --> 31:19.878
Please, don't leave me.

31:23.915 --> 31:25.516
Stay here.
Stay here.

31:25.583 --> 31:26.985
Don't leave me.

31:30.588 --> 31:32.790
I won't be long.
I promise you.

32:39.691 --> 32:42.026
[dog barking]

32:48.666 --> 32:50.668
[electrical zapping]

33:14.892 --> 33:16.794
[high-pitch ringing]

33:30.274 --> 33:33.611
[high-pitch ringing]

33:54.198 --> 33:55.833
<i>Thank you!
You are the best!</i>

33:55.933 --> 33:57.435
<i>[laughing]
Later!</i>

33:57.535 --> 33:58.569
<i>- I want you here at 11:00.
- Bye, Dad.</i>

33:58.636 --> 33:59.904
<i>- Bye-bye, have fun.
- 12:00 then.</i>

34:00.004 --> 34:02.073
<i>You know she played you,
right?</i>

34:02.173 --> 34:03.775
<i>- What?</i>
JAVI:<i> Yeah, she did, Dad.</i>

34:03.841 --> 34:06.077
<i>Dad, look, come here.</i>

34:07.245 --> 34:09.280
<i>- You know what?
- Hm?</i>

34:09.347 --> 34:11.049
- [electrical zapping]
<i>- You've been chumped out.</i>

34:11.115 --> 34:12.884
<i>- What?
- You are a chump.</i>

34:12.950 --> 34:14.552
<i>- What'd you call me?
- No, no! Stop it, I mean it!</i>

34:14.652 --> 34:16.254
<i>- No, put me down, put me down!
- Oh, you think</i>

34:16.320 --> 34:17.588
<i>- you're so funny, right?
- Please, Dad! No!</i>

34:17.688 --> 34:18.723
<i>Come on, put me down!</i>

34:18.790 --> 34:20.124
<i>- No!
- We are going to the fair.</i>

34:20.191 --> 34:21.225
<i>- Be careful! No!
- Okay?</i>

34:21.325 --> 34:23.094
<i>You all think you're so cute</i>

34:23.161 --> 34:24.395
<i>- making fun of your own father.
- Please Dad, No!</i>

34:24.495 --> 34:25.663
<i>Come on, put me down.</i>

34:25.763 --> 34:27.265
<i>It was a joke!
Please!</i>

34:29.567 --> 34:32.103
[Mario sighs deeply]

34:37.475 --> 34:38.876
[sniffling]

34:53.558 --> 34:55.927
[sobbing]

35:17.014 --> 35:19.517
DORA: No! You're lying!
Don't touch me!

35:19.584 --> 35:21.552
ALBERTO: ...absolutely nothing!
DORA: You're such a coward!

35:21.652 --> 35:24.188
- What did you call me?
- I said you're a lying coward!

35:24.288 --> 35:26.190
ALBERTO: Look at me.
Look at me!

35:26.290 --> 35:28.092
[Dora sobbing]

35:34.398 --> 35:36.534
Don't forget the shrimp
for table 12, hurry!

35:36.601 --> 35:38.636
There you go.

35:38.703 --> 35:40.805
[overlapping chatter]

35:44.208 --> 35:46.677
Give me those shrimps
for table 12.

35:46.744 --> 35:47.879
One macchiato
and one ice cream for 10.

35:47.945 --> 35:49.547
Ines, Ines, give him
those napkins, please.

35:49.647 --> 35:51.682
- Check this out, Dad.
- Oh my God, unbelievable.

35:51.749 --> 35:54.285
You always invade all my tables
with your stupid doodles.

35:54.352 --> 35:56.787
But...

35:56.888 --> 35:59.223
[people chattering]

36:34.158 --> 36:36.527
♪♪♪

37:01.786 --> 37:02.486
Damn it!

37:02.553 --> 37:05.156
[grunting]

37:05.223 --> 37:06.824
[rustling]

38:08.686 --> 38:11.055
[keyboard playing]

38:51.529 --> 38:52.730
BEA: I don't understand.
What is this?

38:52.797 --> 38:54.965
- I don't know.
- You didn't know what it was

38:55.032 --> 38:57.168
when you took it
to the library?

38:57.234 --> 38:58.602
Did you open it?

38:58.669 --> 39:00.771
It's just that my grandma
was weird all her life.

39:00.838 --> 39:02.206
You know that, Bea.

39:02.273 --> 39:03.641
But this is...

39:10.748 --> 39:11.015
What's wrong?

39:13.684 --> 39:15.119
BEA: Bring the notebook.

39:17.455 --> 39:19.323
Now, find one
of the red pages.

39:26.464 --> 39:27.631
It's like that game
with magnifying glasses

39:27.732 --> 39:30.568
from the magic book.

39:30.634 --> 39:32.703
This is fucking wicked.

39:38.075 --> 39:40.010
That date is your birthday.

39:52.123 --> 39:54.225
"My granddaughter
was born today.

39:54.325 --> 39:57.762
"I prayed it would be a boy,
but she was born a girl.

39:57.828 --> 40:00.364
"She is cursed, I know.

40:00.431 --> 40:03.667
"She'll inherit my gift
and my malediction.

40:05.803 --> 40:07.638
What the heck is all this?

40:26.424 --> 40:28.592
[shrieking, screaming]

40:28.692 --> 40:29.026
No!

40:54.051 --> 40:56.487
- [alarm blaring]
- They're onto us.

40:56.554 --> 40:58.122
- Run! Run!
- Eva, run!

40:58.189 --> 40:58.923
Ah!
Hurry!

41:29.153 --> 41:32.523
MAN: They found the girls
from Paraiso!

41:36.227 --> 41:37.595
They found them!

41:40.030 --> 41:41.932
The girls from Paraiso!

42:06.123 --> 42:07.091
Sandra?

42:09.560 --> 42:10.895
Sandra!

42:11.529 --> 42:13.764
Sandra!

42:48.265 --> 42:49.433
[Javi gasps]

42:49.533 --> 42:51.035
[electrical zapping]

43:14.391 --> 43:16.760
[alarm blaring]

43:38.282 --> 43:39.984
BEA: "One day,
a boy will be born,

43:40.084 --> 43:43.287
"son of the light
and darkness.

43:43.354 --> 43:45.756
The only one capable of holding
the lodge of shadows in check."

43:45.856 --> 43:47.157
[screaming]

43:47.224 --> 43:48.993
BEA: "The only one
who can defeat them.

43:55.199 --> 43:57.668
- He is the Chosen One."
- [screaming]

43:59.069 --> 44:01.038
"He will awaken evil
and unleash the war."

44:03.474 --> 44:04.775
[screaming]

44:04.842 --> 44:07.211
[alarm blaring]

44:08.412 --> 44:10.314
Run!

44:10.414 --> 44:12.783
[screaming]

44:13.884 --> 44:15.252
[screaming]

44:25.596 --> 44:27.798
SANDRA: Let's go!

44:27.865 --> 44:29.600
[grunting]

44:40.210 --> 44:41.478
Ah!

44:48.285 --> 44:50.654
[screaming]

45:36.734 --> 45:38.135
No! No!

45:38.202 --> 45:39.236
No, please!

45:39.336 --> 45:39.903
No!

45:43.807 --> 45:46.877
No!
Let us go!

45:48.645 --> 45:51.148
♪♪♪

46:47.638 --> 46:48.505
ALVARO: Javi!
QUINO: Javi!

46:48.605 --> 46:50.707
ALVARO: Javi!

46:51.809 --> 46:53.610
- Javi!
- Javi!

46:53.677 --> 46:55.746
Javi! Javi!

46:55.846 --> 46:59.283
[groaning lightly]
Help.

46:59.349 --> 47:01.185
Help.

47:01.285 --> 47:03.554
Come on, help me.

47:03.654 --> 47:05.489
[both grunting]

47:05.556 --> 47:07.891
Let's go.

47:10.561 --> 47:12.930
[panting]

47:38.755 --> 47:42.192
[chanting in local language]

48:35.879 --> 48:37.648
PAULA:<i> Look for the flaw.</i>

48:37.714 --> 48:40.317
<i>Look for what doesn't fit.</i>

48:40.384 --> 48:40.918
<i>The trick.</i>

48:46.156 --> 48:48.759
<i>There's always something
that no one else sees,</i>

48:48.825 --> 48:50.193
<i>but that is there.</i>

48:56.733 --> 48:59.069
♪♪♪
